  "analysis": "The build is successful and doom runs, finding the WAD file and printing startup messages. But it crashes during R_Init with PC=0x0. Likely causes: math stubs causing issues with R_InitColormaps (pow), optimization issues, or memory issues. Let me rebuild with -O0 and add better math stubs, plus debug output.",
  "plan": "1. Rebuild with -O0 to eliminate optimization issues. 2. Improve math stubs. 3. Add debug printf to find exact crash point.",
  "commands": [
    {"keystrokes": "sed -i 's|-O2|-O0|' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/Makefile.mips\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "grep -n 'R_Init\\b' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/r_main.c | head -20\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "sed -n '700,750p' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/r_main.c\n", "duration": 0.1}
  ]
